entity.name: 2022 MTV VMAs
entity.description: The MTV Video Music Awards have wrapped for another year. The 2022 awards saw Taylor Swift win big, with three awards including Video of the Year for All Too Well (10 Minute Version) (Taylor's Version). Lil Nas X and Jack Harlow took away multiple awards for their collaboration INDUSTRY BABY, and Harlow won Song of Summer with First Class. Bad Bunny and BLACKPINK's Lisa made history, with Bad Bunny as the first non-English-language act to take out the Artist of the Year award, and Lisa as the first solo K-Pop artist to win a VMA by winning the Best K-Pop award. Keep it here for all the wins and excitement from the night.
